'''Tanakurahiko Shrine''' (たなくらひこじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Kyōtanabe|Q816728|WD=Q816728|1=Kyōtanabe}}, {{ill|lt=Kyoto Prefecture|Q120730|WD=Q120730|1=Kyoto Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|lt=Shikinaisha major shrine|Q134917288|WD=Q134917288|1=Shikinai Taisha}}, and its former shrine rank was gōsha.

=== History ===
=== Outline ===
According to shrine tradition, it was invited in {{ill|lt=Empress Suiko|Q298057|WD=Q298057|1=Empress Suiko}} 31 ({{ill|lt=623|Q31044|WD=Q31044|1=623}}) from Tanakura-no-shō in {{ill|lt=Sōraku District|Q1154661|WD=Q1154661|1=Sōraku District, Kyoto}}. In the ''{{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}'', it was listed as a major shrine. In the {{ill|lt=Edo period|Q184963|WD=Q184963|1=Edo period}} it was called "Tenmangū." In {{ill|lt=Shōwa|Q327567|WD=Q327567|1=Shōwa era}} 6 ({{ill|lt=1931|Q18782|WD=Q18782|1=1931}}), in {{ill|lt=February|Q109|WD=Q109|1=February}}, it was ranked as a {{ill|lt=gōsha|Q134917316|WD=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}.

=== Divine rank ===
*{{ill|lt=Ten'an (Japan)|Q1075611|WD=Q1075611|lt=Ten'an|1=Ten'an}} 3 ({{ill|lt=859|Q23897|WD=Q23897|1=859}}), {{ill|lt=January 27|Q2284|WD=Q2284|1=January 27}}: promoted from Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade to Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade (''{{ill|lt=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Q1052981|WD=Q1052981|1=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku}}'') - listed as "Tanakurahiko-no-kami"

=== Cultural properties ===
*Main sanctuary ({{ill|lt=Kyoto Prefecture|Q120730|WD=Q120730|1=Kyoto Prefecture}} {{ill|lt=Registered Tangible Cultural Property|Q11579194|WD=Q11579194|1=Registered Tangible Cultural Property of Japan}})
Built in the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Momoyama period|1=UNKNOWN}}.
*Zuiki mikoshi ({{ill|lt=Kyōtanabe|Q816728|WD=Q816728|1=Kyōtanabe}} Intangible Cultural Property)
For the annual festival, a zuiki mikoshi is made using taro stalks, chili peppers, kumquats, globe amaranth, white rice, beans, etc., and it parades through the ujiko district on {{ill|lt=October|Q124|WD=Q124|1=October}} {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Health and Sports Day|1=UNKNOWN}}.

<gallery>
Tanakurahiko Jinja Honden.jpg|Main sanctuary
Zuiki Mikoshi Tanakurahiko Jinja.jpg|Zuiki mikoshi
</gallery>

=== Access ===
*10 minutes on foot from {{ill|lt=Kyōtanabe Station|Q855813|WD=Q855813|1=Kyōtanabe Station}} on the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Gakkentoshi Line|1=UNKNOWN}} of {{ill|lt=West Japan Railway Company|Q502125|WD=Q502125|lt=JR West|1=West Japan Railway Company}}
*15 minutes on foot from {{ill|lt=Shin-Tanabe Station|Q7497135|WD=Q7497135|1=Shin-Tanabe Station}} on the {{ill|lt=Kyoto Line|Q1057349|WD=Q1057349|lt=Kintetsu Kyoto Line|1=Kyoto Line (Kintetsu)}} of {{ill|lt=Kintetsu|Q1531085|WD=Q1531085|lt=Kintetsu Railway|1=Kintetsu Railway}}

